wikipedia_page.main: David Demaine (born 7 May 1942) is a footballer who played as a winger in the Football League for Tranmere Rovers and Southport.In 1965, he played in the Eastern Canada Professional Soccer League with Toronto Roma for two seasons. The remainder of the 1966 season he played in the American Soccer League with Hartford Soccer Club, and later with New York Ukrainians in the German-American Soccer League.In 1967, he played in the National Professional Soccer League with the Toronto Falcons. In 1970, he played in the National Soccer League with the Toronto White Eagles.
